    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-05-27T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-27T01:00:00-05:00" n="23"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d23">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890H.24/86: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Afghanistan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kabul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-27T10:00:00+04:00"
                            >May 27, 1943—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 28—11:08 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>109. Your 45, April 15.<note n="8" xml:id="d23fn8">Not printed.</note> Please
                    inform the War Department that on May 17 the Military Attaché and I officially
                    presented the Dodge army station wagon intended for the King,<note n="9"
                        xml:id="d23fn9">Mohammad Zaher Shah.</note> and on May 25 we presented the
                    Stearman trainer plane intended for the Afghan Air Force. See my telegram 78,
                    September 20, 1942.<note n="8" xml:id="d23fn10">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Both gifts were highly appreciated and I have been requested to convey to the
                    Government of the United States and to the authorities directly concerned the
                    sincere thanks of the Afghan Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
